# Cursor rules maintenance

Applies when changing files under `.cursor/rules/`. Format and placement: [how-to-write-rules.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/how-to-write-rules.mdc).

## Add a new rule when

- A technology or pattern shows up in roughly **three or more** places and agents should default to it
- A preventable bug class keeps appearing
- Reviews repeat the same concrete request

## Change an existing rule when

- Better examples exist in the repo than what the rule shows
- Edge cases or APIs changed and the text is stale
- Another rule was split or renamed—fix references

## Quality bar

- Actionable bullets, not vague slogans
- Examples short and realistic; prefer ❌/✅ only when it prevents misreads
- One main concern per file; split if the file grows hard to scan (~50 lines is a good target)

## Deprecation

- Mark outdated guidance clearly; remove rules that no longer apply
- Update links that pointed at renamed or removed rules
- If behavior changed, add a one-line migration hint when helpful

## Keep docs in sync

- Examples should match current APIs and folder layout
- External doc links should still resolve; prefer stable URLs
